   - As a test, you can use a tool like Postman or a simple HTML form to send a POST request directly to your Google Apps Script URL to see if it handles the request correctly.

By following these steps, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue causing the `doPost` function to not receive the expected data. If you have any specific logs or error messages, please share them for further assistance.

